li.al:
``Agreed services" means scheduled air services
on the routes specified in this Agreement for the transport of passengers
and cargo, including mail, separately or in combination;

``Designated airline" means an airline which
has been designated and authorized in accordance with Articles IV and V of
this Agreement;

``Change of Aircraft" refers to the operation
of one of the agreed services in such a way that one section of the route
is flown by a different aircraft from that used on another section;

a designated airline shall not provide,
or represent itself by advertisement or otherwise as providing, any service
other than an agreed service on the routes specified in this Agreement;

in the event of failure by such airline
to qualify under the laws and regulations normally applied by the aeronautical
authorities of the Contracting Party granting the rights;

in the event of failure by such airline
to comply with the laws and regulations of the Contracting Party granting
the rights;

taken on board aircraft of a designated
airline of one Contracting Party in the territory of the other Contracting
Party;
